messages.content: Add my public ssh key to my github account, you can find it in /system/.ssh.

<function_thought>

The plan is to first read the content of the SSH key file and then use `git_add_ssh_key` to add it to the GitHub account.
First, I need to list the content of the `/system/.ssh` directory to find the public SSH key file.
Then, I will read the content of the public SSH key file.
Finally, I will use `git_add_ssh_key` to add the key.

<function_call>[list_directory(path='/system/.ssh')]</function_call>
